Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
defInShapeBasedDefFile(25.10)                    defInShapeBasedDefFile(25.10)

Name
       defInShapeBasedDefFile

Syntax
        defInShapeBasedDefFile{0 | 1}

       Type: Integer

       Default: 0

       Specifies  that the input file is a shape-based DEF. DEF file generated
       by shape-based router may  contain  overlapping  routing.  By  default,
       defIn drops any overlapping wire segment. Set this variable to 1 if you
       want defIn to consider overlapping wire segments.

       If  the  router of a segment of a metal is connected with the two other
       segments of the same metal, defInShapeBasedDefFile will  consider  this
       as  "overlapping"  metals.  For example, the metal5 segment of net A is
       connected with different length of other metal5 segments of net A. This
       connection will be considered as overlapping metals.

Related Information
